  "content": "lide slide-gap\">\n  <div class=\"slide-inner\">\n    <div class=\"slide-label\">The Problem</div>\n    <div class=\"slide-title\">What's <span class=\"hl-cyan\">Missing</span></div>\n    <div class=\"slide-subtitle\">Three agents. One codebase. Zero shared memory.</div>\n    <div class=\"gap-scenario\">\n      <div class=\"gap-card\" style=\"border-top-color: var(--text-muted);\">\n        <h3 style=\"color: var(--text-muted);\">Isolated</h3>\n        <div class=\"gap-step\">\n          <span class=\"gap-icon\">🤖</span>\n          <div>Agent A redesigns auth across 3 repos</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"gap-step\">\n          <span class=\"gap-icon\">🤖</span>\n          <div>Agent B finds a side effect during testing</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"gap-step\">\n          <span class=\"gap-icon\">❌</span>\n          <div><strong style=\"color: var(--text-primary);\">Agent C starts next week. Knows nothing.</strong></div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"gap-card\" style=\"border-top-color: var(--accent-cyan);\">\n        <h3 style=\"color: var(--accent-cyan);\">Connected</h3>\n        <div class=\"gap-step\">\n          <span class=\"gap-icon\">🤖</span>\n          <div>Agent A redesigns auth → <span class=\"hl-cyan\">recorded</span></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"gap-step\">\n          <span class=\"gap-icon\">🤖</span>\n          <div>Agent B finds side effect → <span class=\"hl-cyan\">recorded</span></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"gap-step\">\n          <span class=\"gap-icon\">✅</span>\n          <div><strong style=\"color: var(--text-primary);\">Agent C queries first. Already knows both.</strong></div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"gap-insight\">\n      That's the difference between personal memory and organizational memory. corvia builds the second layer.\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"footer\">\n      <span>Lim Chun Zhe</span>\n      <span>3 / 10</span>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>",
